cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the use of gradient temporal-difference methods for learning off-policy multiple value functions in parallel, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The use of potential-based shaping rewards is related to control theory, which is covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses real-time learning, which is relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
